cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM, cs.NE 

This paper is about deep learning-based medical image segmentation, which falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) sub-category. The paper also discusses the use of mixed-supervised learning and multi-task learning, which are common techniques in machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The experiments are conducted on medical image datasets, which are typically associated with multimedia (cs.MM) sub-category. Finally, the paper proposes the use of a novel architecture and a recent technique called "Squeeze and Excitation," which are related to neural networks (cs.NE) sub-category.
